{"title":"Blackheart Bike Co’s Slick New Titanium Road Rocket","link":"https://bikerumor.com/blackheart-bike-co-new-titanium-road/","date":1682520363000,"content":"<p>It was pretty cool accidentally running into Zach Lambert, <a href=\"https://blackheartbikeco.com/\" target=\"_blank\">the founder</a> of Blackheart Bike Co. at the food court (if you can even call it that) at this year’s Sea Otter Classic. I was walking by and complimented the Blackheart bike that he was holding (I’ve been following Blackheart’s <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/blackheartbikeco/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a> for a while) and he introduced himself to me and told me about his new modern titanium road model. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, I met him back at his booth and took some photos. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Blackheart Bikes has made it its mission to “support individuals working to make cycling a more welcoming and inclusive sport”. I can get 100% behind that.  </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Blackheart Bike Co Road Ti</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-side.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-side-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Blackheart Bike Co. Road Ti front side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-side-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-side-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-side-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-side-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-side-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-side.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. R. Frazelle</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Zach told me that this new model is all about standing on its own as a truly modern road bike. He didn’t want to simply add to or make a slightly different iteration of an allroad bike that already exists. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-rear-dropouts.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-rear-dropouts-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Blackheart Bike Co. Road Ti rear dropouts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-rear-dropouts-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-rear-dropouts-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-rear-dropouts-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-rear-dropouts-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-rear-dropouts-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-rear-dropouts.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-dropped-seat-stays.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-dropped-seat-stays-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Blackheart Bike Co. Road Ti dropped seat stays\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-dropped-seat-stays-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-dropped-seat-stays-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-dropped-seat-stays-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-dropped-seat-stays-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-dropped-seat-stays-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-dropped-seat-stays.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>He wanted to create a bike that didn’t just recall a classic road bike design, instead, he wanted it to embrace the fully modern road bike in both look and feel. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-end.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-end-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Blackheart Bike Co. Road Ti front end\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-end-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-end-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-end-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-end-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-end-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-front-end.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Ti frame is made of 3/2.5 titanium tubing with a double-butted seat tube. I have to say the bike looks fast just sitting there. It’s got a subtle Kamm tail downtube and a one-piece carbon cockpit with not a cable in sight. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-old-branding.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-old-branding-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Blackheart Bike Co. old branding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-old-branding-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-old-branding-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-old-branding-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-old-branding-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-old-branding-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-old-branding.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Old branding </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-new-branding.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-new-branding-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Blackheart Bike Co. Road Ti new branding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-new-branding-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-new-branding-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-new-branding-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-new-branding-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-new-branding-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-new-branding.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>New Branding</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Zach says the ride is smooth and snappy. It has slippery lines and light understated branding, something that Zach says will be the new branding aesthetic going forward.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-one-piece-carbon-cockpit.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-one-piece-carbon-cockpit-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Blackheart Bike Co. Road Ti one piece carbon cockpit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-one-piece-carbon-cockpit-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-one-piece-carbon-cockpit-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-one-piece-carbon-cockpit-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-one-piece-carbon-cockpit-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-one-piece-carbon-cockpit-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-one-piece-carbon-cockpit.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Road Ti Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-Geometry-Chart.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-Geometry-Chart-800x400.jpeg\" alt=\"Blackheart Bike Co. Road Ti Geometry Chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-Geometry-Chart-800x400.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-Geometry-Chart-297x149.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-Geometry-Chart-120x60.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-Geometry-Chart-768x384.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Blackheart-Bike-Co.-Road-Ti-Geometry-Chart.jpeg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Road Ti Features and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame will come in 9 sizes to fit you better, from 5’0″ to 7’0″.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Fully integrated cables</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Electronic only</li>\n\n\n\n<li>One-piece carbon cockpit</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Carbon fork and seatpost (31.6)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flared top tube</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dropped seat stays</li>\n\n\n\n<li>32mm tire clearance</li>\n\n\n\n<li>T47 bottom bracket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM UDH</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Frame weight (size 54): 1653 grams</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fork weight: 480 grams</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Frameset with carbon fork and seat post: $3000 </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Frameset with carbon fork and seat post and integrated handlebar: $3300</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SRAM Force AXS build w/ Hunt 44 Aerodynamicist carbon wheelset: $7,100</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can check out more details and the other bikes Blackheart has to offer by hitting the link below. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://blackheartbikeco.com/\" target=\"_blank\">BlackheartBikeCo.com</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<p> </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/blackheart-bike-co-new-titanium-road/\">Blackheart Bike Co’s Slick New Titanium Road Rocket</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"dc8a25f07f7e886020d2c3229165b0cd81a9e14122fcb78ac3aea22635c25493","category":"Cycling"}